completion:
To find the matrix for a dilation centered at the origin with a scale factor of \(-3\), we represent the transformation of a point \((x, y)\) as:

\[
\begin{pmatrix}
k & 0 \\
0 & k
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
x \\
y
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
kx \\
ky
\end{pmatrix}
\]

Substituting \(k = -3\):

\[
\begin{pmatrix}
-3 & 0 \\
0 & -3
\end{pmatrix}
\]

Thus, the matrix for a dilation with a scale factor of \(-3\) is:

\[
\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -3 & 0 \\ 0 & -3 \end{pmatrix}}
\]

